    <MissileTemplate>
      <AssociatedTemplateName>SDM-207 astolat</AssociatedTemplateName>
      <Designation>SDM-207</Designation>
      <Nickname>astolat</Nickname>
      <Description>$MISSILEGUIDANCE_MODE_DIRECT - $MISSILESEEKER_MODE_ACTIVE_ABBREV(&lt;color=#3BC81E&gt;RADAR&lt;/color&gt;)/$MISSILESEEKER_MODE_PASSIVE_ABBREV(&lt;color=#D4211D&gt;WAKE&lt;/color&gt;) - $MISSILEWARHEAD_SHORT_BLASTFRAG</Description>
      <LongDescription>The &lt;noparse&gt;SDM-207 astolat&lt;/noparse&gt; is a size 2 direct guidance missile.  It is based on the SDM-2 body, which is a flexible defensive missile with a booster.  This missile will deliver a $MISSILEWARHEAD_DETAIL_BLASTFRAG warhead.  It homes in on its target using an Active Radar seeker  If the primary seeker does not find a target or is jammed, it can fall back on a Passive Wake seeker.

$MISSILESTAT_CONTROLMETHOD: $MISSILEGUIDANCE_MODE_DIRECT
$MISSILESTAT_TARGETINGMODE: &lt;b&gt;&lt;color=#3BC81E&gt;$MISSILESTAT_TARGETINGMODE_POS&lt;/color&gt;	&lt;color=#3BC81E&gt;$MISSILESTAT_TARGETINGMODE_TRACK&lt;/color&gt;&lt;/b&gt;

$MISSILESTAT_PRIMARYSEEKER: $MISSILESEEKER_MODE_ACTIVE_CAPS &lt;color=#3BC81E&gt;RADAR&lt;/color&gt;
